iter at War:A Soviet Journalist with the Red Army, 1941\u20131945|last2=Beevor|first2=Antony|last3=Vinogradova|first3=Luba|publisher=Vintage Books|year=2007|isbn=978-0-307-27533-2|location=New York|last1=Grossman|first1=Vasili\u012d Semenovich}}* Hellbeck, Jochen. (2015) ''Stalingrad: The City That Defeated The Third Reich''. New York, NY: PublicAffairs. {{ISBN|978-1-61039-496-3}}.\n* {{Citation | last = Hill | first = Alexander | title = The Red Army and the Second World War | publisher = Cambridge University Press | year = 2017 | isbn = 978-1-1070-2079-5}}.\n* Jones, Michael K. (2007) ''Stalingrad: How the Red Army Survived the German Onslaught.'' Drexel Hill, PA: Casemate, (hardcover, {{ISBN|978-1-932033-72-4}}).\n* Joly, Anton (2013) ''Stalingrad Battle Atlas'', StalData Publications (paperback, {{ISBN|979-10-93222-03-5}}).\n* [[Geoffrey Roberts|Roberts, Geoffrey]]. (2002) ''Victory at Stalingrad: The Battle that Changed History''. New York: Longman, (paperback, {{ISBN|0-582-77185-4}}).\n{{Refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikisource|Adolf Hitler's Stalingrad Speech}}\n{{Wikisource|Adolf Hitler's Proclamation on the 10th Anniversary of Coming to Power (30 January 1943)}}\n* [http://www.militaryhistoryonline.com/wwii/stalingrad/default.aspx Detailed summary of campaign]\n* [http://www.awesomestories.com/history/battle-stalingrad Story of the Stalingrad battle with pictures, maps, video and other primary and secondary sources]\n* [http://panorama.volgadmin.ru/ Volgograd State Panoramic Museum official homepage]\n* [http://www.columbia.edu/~lnp3/mydocs/culture/Battle_of_Stalingrad.htm The Battle of Stalingrad in Film and History] Written with strong Socialist/Communist political under and overtones.\n* Roberts, Geoffrey. [https://www.theguardian.com/comment/story/0,3604,904535,00.html \"Victory on the Volga\"], ''[[The Guardian]]'', 28 February 2003\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20081209035540/http://www.stalingrad-info.com/ Stalingrad-info.com, Russian archival 